[card]Calming Licid[/card] is our first licid, and it sees play in 11 decks. Here's what you need to know about licids: they have the ability to change types in response to spells and abilities. Similar to how the gods of Theros can gain or lose their creature status, a licid can pay a cost and become a creature or an enchantment. If someone attempts to blow up up your Calming Licid with a [card]Murder[/card], you can pay a white, tap it, and pop it onto your opponen'ts [card]Drana, Liberator of Malakir[/card] as an aura, and the Murder will fizzle because it doesn't have a valid target. If another player tries to get rid of the licid from Drana with a [card]Forsake the Worldly[/card], you can pay a white to make the licid is a 2/2 creature again, and Forsake the Wordly will fizzle for lack of a valid target. Something to note, though, while a licid can change its type, changing type does not make it a new object, so cards like [card]Anguished Unmaking[/card] and [card]Utter End[/card] can still track it, and exile it, regardless of whether it's a creature or an enchantment. Additionally, changing its type back and forth will not give it summoning sickness.
